7.72	CIWS	Close-in weapon system	A close-in weapon system (CIWS), often pronounced sea-whiz, is a naval shipboard point-defense weapon for detecting and destroying at short range incoming anti-ship missiles and enemy aircraft which have penetrated the outer defenses.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/19/Close-In_Weapon_System.jpg/200px-Close-In_Weapon_System.jpg
